title: California Firm Recalls Boneless Beef Products Imported Without Benefit of Inspection
summary: WASHINGTON, January 7, 2015 Jinon Corporation, dba Nijiya Market, a Torrance, Calif. establishment, is recalling approximately 359 pounds of frozen boneless beef products produced in Japan that were not presented at the U.S. point of entry for inspection, the U.S. Department of Agricultures Food Safety...
